main event: A civilian couple observed four grey, round objects over Chicago, which vanished after a few minutes.
interesting points: The objects were described as being the size of a silver dollar., Police officers reported seeing a deep reddish-orange object that descended rapidly., The observed objects moved in a straight line without making any sound., Five reports of unidentified fluorescent flying objects were noted south of Chicago., Siting durations varied, with some objects observed for up to 15 minutes.
witness description: a civilian couple and two police officers
